1 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
1
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1-712.2 of Title 63, unless
2
3 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
3
4 A. A hospital, medical facility, or long-term care facility
4
5 licensed by the State Department of Health shall establish policies
5
6 and procedures necessary to track and document all additions,
6
7 deletions, and other edits to a patient’s medical records.
7
8 B. Any person shall have the right to obtain, upon request,
8
9 detailed information of all additions, deletions, and other edits to
9
10 his or her medical records made by a hospital, medical facility, or
10
11 long-term care facility, or those of:
11
12 1. A minor child of whom the person is the parent or legal
12
13 guardian; or
13
14 2. Any other patient who lacks capacity to make medical
14
15 decisions and for whom the person has legal authority to make such
15
16 decisions and would have legal access to the patient’s medical
16
17 records.
17
18 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
